Business Brief -- Pharmaceutical Resources Inc.:
   Profit of $673,000 Is Posted
   For the Fiscal First Quarter
Net for the latest quarter included an extraordinary tax
credit of $250,000, or two cents a share. The year-ago loss
included a loss from discontinued operations of $2.3 million,
or 20 cents a share. In September, the company decided to
discontinue the operations of its Quad Pharmaceuticals unit.
The 1990 results were reclassified to state separately the
results of discontinued operations.
   Pharmaceutical Resources shares closed yesterday at $7.25,
up 12.5 cents, in New York Stock Exchange composite trading.